title: Deja vu: Vulcan Centaur rocket powers through 'significant performance anomaly' on satellite launch
description: A Vulcan Centaur rocket successfully launched two U.S. spy satellites on Feb. 12 despite suffering an anomaly with one of its solid rocket boosters, echoing the result of an October 2024 mission.
